                <Gloss>to move from one place to another</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to change one’s location</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to depart</Gloss>
                <Gloss>departure</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In view of the specific reference of μετάθεσις in {S:05801100500038}, it is possible to speak of ‘being taken up,’ but the meaning is clearly a significant change of location from one place to another, that is to say, from earth to heaven.</Comments>
